Senate Sets Panetta Defense Confirmation Hearing for June 9

-- B y   T o n y   C a p a c c i o
-- 
2011-06-02T21:27:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/senate-sets-panetta-defense-confirmation-hearing-for-june-9.html
The Senate Armed Services Committee
will hold a confirmation hearing June 9 for Leon Panetta,
President  Barack Obama ’s nominee to succeed Defense Secretary
 Robert Gates .  Gates’s last day in office will be June 30, the White House
announced in April. The committee announced today the
confirmation hearing date.  Panetta is currently director of the Central Intelligence
Agency. Obama has nominated Army General David Petraeus, the top
U.S. commander in  Afghanistan , to be the next CIA director.  If confirmed to their new posts by the Senate, Panetta and
Petraeus will be in position to follow through on security
objectives facing Obama as he heads into an election year.  Panetta, 72, is a California Democrat who served in the
U.S. House of Representatives from 1977 to 1993 and then as
budget director and White House chief of staff in the Clinton
administration. He has been CIA director since February 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Capaccio in Washington at 
 acapaccio@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
